One additional thing I noticed when I saw this code once again after a while @bstansberry :
There is a potential problem but as I'm not sure what forced task really is I'm not sure is it intended or just another bug:
This code:
        while ((task = taskQueue.poll()) != null) {
            if (task.forceRun) {
                forcedTask = task;
            } else {
                storage.add(task);
            }
        }
will go trough all tasks in taskQueue so there is potential problem of dropping forced tasks if there is more than one. Only last forced task will be returned to a caller, previous ones are not added to a storage collection so they are just lost.

